title: Lana Del Rey Almost Named Her Latest Album Bird World
text:
Photo: Jesse Grant/Getty Images

Bird World? Excuse me, BIRD WORLD?! Lana Del Rey dropped a bombshell while discussing her latest album, Norman Fucking Rockwell! with producer Jack Antonoff. Apparently, one of the titles considered for the mood record about unstable women and the fuckboys who try to love them was Bird World. Which means, if the multiverse theory of reality is true, there is a parallel universe somewhere out there where Lana Del Rey just released an album implicitly about a world of birds. Do the Beatles exist in this universe? Who’s to say! Was Tuca & Bertie given a second season in this reality? Almost certainly. It’s the birds’ world, after all.

oh my god lana del rey almost named her album bird world



holy shit pic.twitter.com/g8TWf2lCCK — leon (@leyawn) September 5, 2019

There is a YouTube channel that remixes films and television shows to LDR’s music. The choices are not intuitive, but they are art of the highest form. I’m going to need this auteur to mix a track off Shoulda Been Called “Bird World” to footage of birds from Planet Earth immediately. Maybe “Cinnamon Girl.” I don’t think I’m being hyperbolic in saying it could easily end world hunger.
description: Lana Del Rey was speaking to Jack Antonoff, promoting their album together: Norman Fucking Rockwell! Apparently, Del Rey almost named the album Bird World, which is an insane name. Norman Fucking Rockwell’s first single was “Venice Bitch.”
